01:05.063 --> 01:06.998
St. Charles place.

01:07.066 --> 01:09.634
Wanna buy it ?
How much is it ?

01:09.702 --> 01:11.870
It's $140, Edith.
Can't you read there ?

01:12.938 --> 01:15.140
Well, I-I don't know.

01:15.207 --> 01:17.976
Uh, uh, what do
you think, Gloria ?

01:19.078 --> 01:21.012
Well, you already own
states Avenue.

01:21.080 --> 01:23.081
This'll give you
two-thirds of a monopoly.

01:23.149 --> 01:25.316
Aw, come on, Edith.
Will ya make up
your own mind.

01:25.384 --> 01:27.318
Make your own decisions,
ya know.

01:27.386 --> 01:30.021
In the real world, you don't go
to your competition for advice.

01:30.089 --> 01:34.492
- She's not in the real world.
It's only a game.
- So is life a game, buddy boy.

01:36.062 --> 01:38.496
Whether you play
the game in here
or out there,

01:38.564 --> 01:40.865
you gotta play it
to win, right ?

01:40.933 --> 01:43.401
Where did we
hear that, Archie ?

01:43.468 --> 01:46.571
Was it on <i>mannix</i>
<i>or</i> <i>the bold ones</i> ?

01:49.041 --> 01:51.743
Keep your mind
on your property,
huh, Edith ?

01:51.811 --> 01:56.147
"Whether it's
this game in here
or that game out there--"

01:56.215 --> 01:58.516
you wanna buy
St. Charles's place ?

02:01.320 --> 02:03.654
I'll take it.

02:03.723 --> 02:05.924
Whoopee. The dingbat
makes a decision.

02:09.895 --> 02:12.663
Twenty, thirty,
forty, fifty--

02:12.732 --> 02:15.600
what are you countin'
the tens for ? You got
a pile of hundreds.

02:15.667 --> 02:17.869
Here's a hundred.
Gimme four tens.
There's $140.

02:17.937 --> 02:20.071
Put it in the bank.
Let's go, huh ?

02:20.139 --> 02:22.073
Come on, daddy.
Stop nagging at her.

02:22.141 --> 02:24.209
And you haven't answered
Michael's question yet.

02:24.276 --> 02:27.578
- Are you going with him to the
blood bank tomorrow morning ?
- The blood bank ? No.

02:27.646 --> 02:29.580
Reading railroad.
I'll buy it.

02:29.648 --> 02:33.684
- Why not, arch ? You said
last week you'd go with me.
- I changed my mind.

02:33.753 --> 02:37.789
I ain't givin' none of my blood
unless I know who's gonna be
on the receivin' end of it.

02:37.857 --> 02:39.958
Hey, well,
what's the difference ?

02:40.025 --> 02:44.062
The difference is,
some radical blows up
a building, right ?

02:44.130 --> 02:46.697
He gets shot;
He needs a transfusion.

02:46.766 --> 02:49.734
Well, he ain't gonna get
none of Archie bunker's blood !

02:52.071 --> 02:54.939
Neither is anybody else,
I got a feelin'.

02:55.007 --> 02:58.509
I think you're right, Michael.
That's just an excuse, daddy.

02:58.577 --> 03:01.679
Tennessee Avenue.
My property.
The rent is $14.

03:01.747 --> 03:03.681
Let's have it.
All right.
I'll give it to you.

03:03.749 --> 03:05.784
Relax there.
Don't act so pushy.

03:05.851 --> 03:09.553
I don't know why he won't
give blood. He never gives
anything to anybody.

03:09.621 --> 03:11.722
[ Sneezing ]

03:11.791 --> 03:13.992
He gave me
this cold I got.

03:16.595 --> 03:18.529
All right, here we go
for a roll now.

03:18.597 --> 03:23.601
He's always givin' me colds.
Over the years, he's given me
a lot of colds.

03:23.669 --> 03:25.670
Edith, I'm tryin'
to roll over here, huh ?

03:25.737 --> 03:29.674
It's all right for him
when he gets a cold.
He's the husband.

03:29.741 --> 03:32.510
He can take time off
and go to bed with it.

03:32.577 --> 03:34.512
Edith, I'm tryin'
to roll here.

03:34.579 --> 03:37.782
While I'm runnin' up
and down stairs,
waitin' on him--

03:44.223 --> 03:46.390
but when I get
a cold--

03:49.628 --> 03:54.165
I'm the wife.
I can't take time off.
I can't go to bed.

03:54.233 --> 03:56.801
Will you
stifle yourself.
[ Sniffles, sneezes ]

03:56.869 --> 03:58.803
Oh--

03:58.871 --> 04:01.005
why do you do that ?

04:01.073 --> 04:04.976
You know I'm very, very
susceptible of colds, Edith.

04:05.044 --> 04:08.880
Really, now.
I mean, ever since the war--
the big one.

04:08.948 --> 04:10.882
It happened because
I was sleepin' in...

04:10.950 --> 04:13.818
Them wet tents all the time,
with the rain pourin' in on me.

04:13.886 --> 04:16.687
All right, Archie. Not the
"big war" routine again, huh ?

04:16.755 --> 04:19.690
The big war made
a lot of people very sick.

04:23.329 --> 04:26.530
- I get a cold
every winter this time--
- all right, Archie. We know.

04:26.598 --> 04:30.134
You get the only war-connected
head colds in the country.

04:30.202 --> 04:32.971
- Now, will you
roll the dice, please ?
- All right, I'm rollin'.

04:33.038 --> 04:34.973
Here we go.
There we are.

04:35.040 --> 04:36.975
One, two, three,
four, five, six.

04:37.042 --> 04:39.010
Park place. Right next
to the boardwalk.

04:39.078 --> 04:41.746
That's the best monopoly
on the board. Come on.
Okay, 350. 350.

04:41.813 --> 04:43.814
Here you are.
Five hundred.
Change.
All right.

04:43.883 --> 04:46.384
Here's your deed.
All right.
Ha-ha-ha.

04:46.451 --> 04:49.187
Look at him gloating.
You'd think
he was really rich.

04:49.255 --> 04:51.189
Yeah, well,
I am rich.

04:51.257 --> 04:54.625
A man is rich who can
enjoy himself in the bosom
of his family, huh ?

04:59.531 --> 05:01.933
You sure are
shovelin' it tonight, arch.

05:07.139 --> 05:11.409
"A man is rich
who can enjoy himself--"

05:11.476 --> 05:13.778
you know who said that ?

05:13.845 --> 05:16.247
Marcus welby, m.D.

05:19.351 --> 05:23.254
- Will you roll, huh ?
- I wanna ask you
something, Archie.

05:23.322 --> 05:25.356
That, uh, guy that you
wouldn't give blood to.

05:25.424 --> 05:27.758
The radical who got shot
blowin' up a building ?

05:27.826 --> 05:30.094
<i>Yeah ?</i>
<i>How do you know</i>
<i>that the blood</i>
<i>he finally gets...</i>

05:30.162 --> 05:32.096
Won't be
William Buckley's ?

05:32.164 --> 05:34.399
Because--
oh !

05:34.466 --> 05:37.068
I gotta go to jail.

05:37.136 --> 05:39.070
Good.

05:40.339 --> 05:43.674
Make it
solitary confinement, huh ?

05:43.742 --> 05:47.278
Because bill Buckley
would never give
no blood of his...

05:47.346 --> 05:49.880
To some radical who was
blowin' up buildings.

05:49.949 --> 05:53.318
Archie, if Buckley's blood
is in a bank,
he's not gonna know.

05:53.385 --> 05:56.587
Well, he might not know,
but down at the blood bank,
they know.

05:56.655 --> 05:59.190
They got names
on all the jars.
No, they don't.

05:59.258 --> 06:01.225
Oh, he doesn't get
the concept, Michael.

06:01.293 --> 06:04.829
Look, daddy, blood is blood.
It's all the same,
no matter who it comes from.

06:04.896 --> 06:08.032
<i>[ Mocking ] "No matter</i>
<i>who it comes from."</i>
<i>You hear that ?</i>

06:08.100 --> 06:10.068
You send 'em out to get
a normal education,

06:10.135 --> 06:12.070
they come back with
all these subversions.

06:12.137 --> 06:14.538
Where do they
get it, huh, Edith ?

06:14.606 --> 06:16.941
Huh ?
I can't talk.

06:17.009 --> 06:19.043
I'm in solitary.

06:25.851 --> 06:27.785
Well, let me
tell you somethin',
little girl.

06:27.853 --> 06:31.055
Blood is like anything else
in life. You got your good
and you got your bad.

06:31.123 --> 06:34.292
You do not know
what you're talking about.
All right.

06:34.360 --> 06:37.428
For instance,
John dillinger
had bad blood.

06:38.797 --> 06:40.731
John dillinger ?
Who is John dillinger ?

06:40.799 --> 06:42.833
Aw, gee.
Listen to this guy.

06:42.901 --> 06:47.071
He's arguin' blood,
he don't even know
who John dillinger is.

06:47.139 --> 06:49.840
You're over your head,
Sonny boy.
Get outta the water.

06:49.908 --> 06:51.909
Look, Archie,
I-I don't wanna argue with you.

06:51.977 --> 06:54.712
I'm just stating a fact.
All blood is the same.

06:54.779 --> 06:57.982
Well, if all blood is the same,
let me ask you this:

06:58.050 --> 07:01.185
How come they ain't got
no swedes in the mafia ?

07:06.392 --> 07:09.560
What does that got to do
with anything ?

07:09.628 --> 07:14.932
Because your Italians got
a lock on it, that's why.
It's in their blood.

07:15.000 --> 07:18.403
The same way it's in
your blacks' blood to do
the Scooby-dooby-doo.

07:18.470 --> 07:20.938
Aw, jeez !
Oh, that's terrible !

07:21.006 --> 07:23.574
Daddy !
That's true !
It's not true !

07:23.642 --> 07:25.709
[ Stammering ]
What I'm telling you,
Archie,

07:25.777 --> 07:27.945
is an accepted
scientific fact.

07:28.013 --> 07:30.048
You take any two pints
of blood,
yeah, any two.

07:30.115 --> 07:32.050
Uh, one from Asia,
one from America--

07:32.117 --> 07:34.318
or one from a black man
and one from a white man.
Yeah.

07:34.386 --> 07:36.954
Any two pints of blood,
and assumin' that both donors
are healthy,

07:37.022 --> 07:39.957
and the types match,
those two pints of blood
are interchangeable.

07:40.025 --> 07:44.128
Yeah, because chemically
they're exactly the same.
Right, exactly.

07:44.196 --> 07:47.231
Are you both finished ?
[ Mike ]
Yeah.

07:47.299 --> 07:49.900
You want my reaction ?

07:49.968 --> 07:51.969
Commie propaganda,
pure and simple.

07:52.037 --> 07:55.506
Oh-- oh !
That's bull !

07:55.574 --> 07:58.409
That's straight
from the russkies,
right off the kremlin line !

07:58.477 --> 08:00.611
Archie, Archie,
what I am tellin' you...

08:00.679 --> 08:02.613
I'm gonna tell you
for the last time.

08:02.681 --> 08:06.384
Any man's blood will work
in any other man's body, period.
That's a fact.

08:06.452 --> 08:08.486
College life
has got youse two--
all right, daddy--

08:08.554 --> 08:11.989
you two are sick !
I'm talkin' science !
This is a scientific fact !

08:12.057 --> 08:14.992
You don't argue
with science !
It's my turn !

